r four- to five-year-olds.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/44.mp3","time_start":127.6,"time_end":132.21},{"position":45,"content":"She's quite mature for her age and she can already write her name and read a little.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/45.mp3","time_start":132.21,"time_end":136.6},{"position":46,"content":"Well, I'll put her in the red group","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/46.mp3","time_start":136.6,"time_end":138.9},{"position":47,"content":"and we can always change her to the green one if there are any problems.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/47.mp3","time_start":138.9,"time_end":142.39},{"position":48,"content":"That sounds fine.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/48.mp3","time_start":142.39,"time_end":143.83},{"position":49,"content":"OK.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/49.mp3","time_start":143.83,"time_end":144.63},{"position":50,"content":"Let's move on to meals.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/50.mp3","time_start":144.63,"time_end":146.65},{"position":51,"content":"We can provide breakfast, lunch and dinner.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/51.mp3","time_start":146.65,"time_end":149.36},{"position":52,"content":"As she's finishing pretty early, she won't need dinner,","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/52.mp3","time_start":149.61,"time_end":152.69},{"position":53,"content":"will you give her breakfast before she comes?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/53.mp3","time_start":152.76,"time_end":155.05},{"position":54,"content":"Yes, she'll only need lunch.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/54.mp3","time_start":155.05,"time_end":157.26},{"position":55,"content":"Now, does she have any medical conditions we need to know about?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/55.mp3","time_start":158.02,"time_end":161.68},{"position":56,"content":"Does she have asthma or any hearing problems for example?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/56.mp3","time_start":161.68,"time_end":165.38},{"position":57,"content":"No. But she does need to wear glasses.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/57.mp3","time_start":165.6,"time_end":168.21},{"position":58,"content":"Oh, I'll make a note of that.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/58.mp3","time_start":168.21,"time_end":170.13},{"position":59,"content":"Yes, she's pretty good about wearing them, she can't see much without them.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/59.mp3","time_start":170.5,"time_end":174.01},{"position":60,"content":"Right. OK.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/60.mp3","time_start":174.01,"time_end":175.64},{"position":61,"content":"Now, I also need emergency contact details.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/61.mp3","time_start":175.76,"time_end":179.06},{"position":62,"content":"So what sort of information do you need?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/62.mp3","time_start":179.17,"time_end":181.47},{"position":63,"content":"Just the name and number of a friend or family member we can contact in case we can't get hold of you at any time.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/63.mp3","time_start":181.68,"time_end":188.04},{"position":64,"content":"OK.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/64.mp3","time_start":188.36,"time_end":189.28},{"position":65,"content":"That'd better be my sister... Jenny Ball.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/65.mp3","time_start":189.59,"time_end":192.96},{"position":66,"content":"That's B-A-L-L.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/66.mp3","time_start":192.96,"time_end":195.32},{"position":67,"content":"Her phone number is 33467523.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/67.mp3","time_start":195.56,"time_end":201.52},{"position":68,"content":"Great.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/68.mp3","time_start":201.52,"time_end":202.36},{"position":69,"content":"So she is the child's aunt?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-10-test-3-part-1-2023-06-14-12-30-36/69.mp3","time_start":202.36,"time_end":204.62},{"position":70,"content":"Yes, that's right."